penguinsrule66 at 2009-11-30 14:16 CET:
Burned twice, tried to install three times with each burn. Every time, blue screened at starting Windows during install. Attempting to install as second os in a dual boot Win7/XP environment. It didn't work for me.

Did you have Windows 7 already installed? If So, go back and install XP first. If that's not an option, After installing XP (if it installs correctly for you) Repair your Windows 7 install to ensure that the boot files are created properly.
any news on windows update?

@penguinsrule
When setting up a dual-boot between vista/7 and XP you have to install XP first and then Vista or if you're doing it on two separate HDDs (rather than two partitions) you can pull it off by switching the boot sequence between the two HDDs but that's a royal pain.  But if you're trying to pull this off on a single drive you MUST install XP then Vista.
